Text: To get this working I had to do 'sudo chmod -R 755' to the app. Without the app wouldn't open.
Would mind explaining how to do this in terminal.  Thanks!
could you explain how to use the terminal to do this?  thanks!

How to use terminal to open: Open Temrinal, type in 'sudo chmod -R 755' (without the ') and the a space, then go to CORE Keygen in finder, and drag the application into terminal, it will autamically generate a string of folder shortcuts in terminal. Now hit enter. enter your password if it asks. Now open the app and it will actualy open now
